person_summary.description:
We will keep your dogs active! Fenced in backyard + neighborhood park in walking distance + car to take your dogs on hikes or to nearby dog parks as requested! We are very close to Golden Gardens and Discovery Park.

*** Before booking, and when considering drop off and pick up times, please keep in mind that we both work full time during the week Monday-Friday, roughly 9am-5pm. Please contact us to ask about specific dates and times before booking! Also take note that we do have a large, but very friendly, dog in the house.***

When you book a service with us, you will have two experienced pet lovers to look after your loved ones! Madison (a librarian) and Devin (an attorney) are a couple that have had dogs in their families since childhood. Our home in Ballard is fenced in, and we pull out the kiddie pool for dogs to play in on warmer days! We are currently parents to a Great Pyrenees (she is the sweetest!). Madison has previous experience as a regular dog & house sitter for several families during college, and Devin's family has had no less than 3-4 dogs for many years. We know how important our furry friends are to a family! We will treat your pet as if it were our own, with love, affection, and care. 

We love all breeds and have experience with: Great Pyrenees, Doodles, Corgis, Terriers, Labs, Huskies, and lots of mixes.

We are happy to set up a meet and greet so you can meet us both, get a feel for our personalities, and to see if we're a good fit for you and your pets! As pet owners who use Rover ourselves, we know how nerve wracking it can be to leave your pet or home in the hands of other people. Our goal is for you to be as worry free as possible as we take care of your pet. We promise clear and regular communication, with status and photo updates!

provider_profile.requested_dog_info:
We love all breeds! 

If your dog will be staying/visiting our home for overnight pet sitting or doggy day care:

1. Does your dog enjoy the company of other dogs? We have a 100 pound Great Pyrenees (female, spayed). She is extremely well socialized with other dogs and is a big softie. We are happy to set up a meet and a greet between our pooches to prove it to ya!
2. For doggy day care, we will accept up to 3 dogs at a time from different families. Let us know if this would be an issue for your dog.

If we come to your home, we will NOT be bringing our dog with us.

Things we'd like to know:
1. Any quirks, preferences, or behavior issues we should be aware of.
2. Are your pets okay around other animals and people? This will be helpful to know if we go on walks together.
3. Would you like for us to do anything around your house (refill water or food, bring in mail, etc) - please ask!
4. Do you have other expectations for us? We want to make sure that you are satisfied!

person_summary.description:
Hello Fellow Fur Baby Lovers! 

My name is Janet, and I have been around dogs and cats my whole life.  I grew up with a Border Collie named, Gypsy, who was with us for 15 years, along with Putty, the cat, for six.  In addition, my ex-husband and I had two, Kelpies, for a few years (he moved with the dogs), so am used to being around high energy pups :)

I have owned a house, in the North Beach section of Ballard, for the last 10+ years.  My home contains a Mother-in-Law apartment, along with a fully fenced, 7000 square foot yard, and I have only rented to dog owners.  I had always provided backup care for my four legged tenants, and also walk and have dog sat over the years. The apartment is now an Airbnb, in which dogs are allowed, of course!!! In addition, I've been a volunteer at PAWS in Lynnwood for 8 months, and thoroughly enjoy walking, and snuggling with a wide variety of pups....Pits, Retrievers, Collies, Chihuahuas, Terriers, you name it.   

Also, I have a few places where your "kids" can sleep.  I usually sleep with the dogs in my bed, but many prefer to sleep solo.  Therefore, I have provided a couple of beds around if they feel like alone time.  

Folks that have known my special connection to dogs and cats, have often called me the animal whisperer, due to my ability to gain the trust of a fur baby in a short period of time.  You and your baby, will be in very goods hands with me.  I hope you trust me to tend to their care, as you will not be disappointed!!!

Cheers,
Janet

We are true dog lovers who will shower your dog with tender loving care.  If you want your dog to be obsessed over, we are your people! We went through a lot with our previous dogs and cared for them through their vulnerable golden years. We are experts at caring for high needs dogs, such as oldies with mobility issues. Younger ones who enjoy extra attention are welcome, too! So that our dogs wouldn't have to struggle with stairs, we built a ramp to the backyard. It is because we had such a hard time finding extra-attentive sitters for our own dogs that we joined Rover. Dog owner and dog/animal lover since childhood where I grew up on a small working farm with horses, cats, dogs, chickens and rabbits. 
I have a friendly spayed Bernese mountain dog, Talulah, who loves playing with all sized dogs who gets excited when people come to the door. Feel free to contact me directly if you have dates that arent open on my calendar or if you have two dogs rather than my preferred one extra dog. Looking forward to hearing from you.

reviews.content: Our dog had a wonderful time for 6 days with Gayane, Sona and their 2 fur friends! I would highly recommend their family as a great place for your fur baby if you have to leave town. They sent lots of photos, took lots of walks and when I picked up my pup, he was as happy as ever!!

Gayane is a very loving and caring person.
For how long I have known her she always had dogs or her children had dogs and she always took a great care of the dogs: feeding, walking, brushing and cleaning, etc.

Gayane's my mother. So to keep the reader from thinking that I am biased, I will just write a few facts here about her and her life. 
- We had a dog, Fluke - an apricot poodle, who lived with us for 18 years. Though he was gifted to me and my sister, he would always be attached to my mom most of all of us. He would recognize her by "mom", will let only her to bath and give him a haircut. And only my mom was able to take his food from the front of him. No one else could dare.
- Despite the vaccinations, Fluke got sick when he was a puppy. Thought the vet was doubting whether it makes sense to keep treating Fluke, my mom insisted on the treatment and spent a dozen of sleepless nights with him. The dog survived and lived with us through long and happy 18 years. 
- My mother grew up in a family, where there was always a dog.  All of them loved her dearly. For some funny reason, my grandpa would call all of them - Rex. Rex I, Rex II, Rex III.
- Currently my mom lives with my sister in Seattle, and looks after her 2 dogs as well, when she and her husband are working. Daisy and Astrid adore her - they prefer to sleep in her room and frustrate the hell out of my sister.
- My mother is a super caring person with a strong character - and this goes beyond dogs. She raised 2 girls on her own, through hell and high water. My sister is now a software developer in Amazon, I work for a CEO of a listed company in Europe. We both got double education due to her support and willingness to go for the extra mile. 
- Another fact to support the point about caring beyond animals: at some point despite being a scientist and due to economic difficulties in our home-country, she had to work as a baby-sitter. In 2-3 years she did so well, that she was invited to be the baby-sitter for the children of Prime Minister of the country. 

Gayane would like to do the dog-sitting primarily because she likes to spend her time caring for them.

person_summary.description:
Jae and I would love to have our own fur baby one day, but as of now, we are excited to be taking care of yours! We are flexible and accommodating to you and your dog's needs. We will run with your dog, go on hikes if your dog is feeling up for it, wonder and sniff around in parks if your dog desires, and take your dog to a lake/beach for a swim if your dog is a swimmer! We would be more than happy to keep you updated with texts and pictures, so you know your dog is safe and having fun! Tell us about your dog - likes and dislikes; quirks and habits; and favorite treats! We are listening and down for lots of fun!

About our schedule: 
Jae and I have alternating schedules. We try to make sure one of us is always home when we have a furry guest. 

Regarding the number of dogs we host: 
We take 1-2 dogs at a time, but if you prefer your dog to be the only guest, please let us know. If there is no booking already, we'd be happy to block out the calendar for you.

We may not be a good fit if your dog has the following trait(s):
1) Persistent barking 
2) Separation anxiety
3) Urine-marking behavior indoors
4) Not potty trained 
5) Not up-to-date on vaccinations, not flea-free

Before booking...
We would like to schedule a meet and greet to make sure we will be a good fit for your dog(s). Please let us know what day/time works best for you.
